(3358, 34, '2017-02-18 16:04:55', '2017-02-18 16:04:55', '[{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"What is Diabetes?\",\"lhsI\":\"Diabetes%20is%20a%26nbsp%3Blife-long%20health%20condition%20in%20which%20the%20body%20either%20cannot%20produce%20insulin%20or%20cannot%20properly%20use%20the%20insulin%20it%20produces.%20Insulin%20is%20a%20hormone%20that%20controls%20the%20amount%20of%20glucose%20%28sugar%29%20in%20the%20blood.%20Diabetes%20leads%20to%20high%20blood%20sugar%20levels%2C%20which%20can%20damage%20organs%2C%20blood%20vessels%20and%20nerves.%20There%20are%202%20types%20of%20Diabetes%20which%20are%20type%201%20and%20type%202.\",\"rhsI\":\"\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"what is the problem?\",\"lhsI\":\"In%20type%201%20diabetes%2C%20the%20body%20does%20not%20produce%20the%20insulin%20because%26nbsp%3Bthe%20immune%20system%20mistakenly%20attacks%20and%20kills%20the%26nbsp%3Bcells%20responsible%20for%20its%20production.\",\"rhsI\":\"Type%202%20diabetes%20occurs%20when%20the%20body%20can%26rsquo%3Bt%20properly%20use%20the%20insulin%20that%20is%20produced%20or%20does%20not%20make%20enough%20insulin.%26nbsp%3B\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Incidence\",\"lhsI\":\"About%205%26nbsp%3Bto%2010%25%26nbsp%3Bof%20people%20with%20diabetes%20have%20type%201%20diabetes.%20Type%201%20diabetes%20generally%20develops%20in%20childhood%20or%20adolescence%2C%20but%20can%20develop%20in%20adulthood.%26nbsp%3B\",\"rhsI\":\"Type%202%20diabetes%20accounts%20for%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20people%20who%20have%20diabetes-90%20to%2095%25.More%20often%20it%20develops%20in%20adults%2C%20but%20children%20can%20be%20affected.%26nbsp%3B\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Treatment\",\"lhsI\":\"Type%201%20diabetes%20is%20always%20treated%20with%20insulin.\",\"rhsI\":\"Depending%20on%20the%20severity%20of%20type%202%20diabetes%2C%20it%20may%20be%20managed%20through%20physical%20activity%20and%20meal%20planning%2C%20or%20may%20also%20require%20medications%20and/or%20insulin%20to%20control%20blood%20sugar%