(3426, 36, '2017-02-25 17:18:10', '2017-02-25 17:18:10', '<p>[{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"Computer%20Science%20is%20the%20study%20of%20how%20data%20and%20instructions%20are%20processed%2C%20stored%2C%20communicated%20by%20computing%20devices.%20A%20modern%20descendant%20of%20Applied%20Mathematics%20and%20Electrical%20Engineering%2C%20Computer%20Science%20deals%20with%20algorithms%20for%20processing%20data%2C%20the%20symbolic%20representation%20of%20data%20and%20instructions%2C%20the%20design%20of%20instruction%20languages%20for%20processing%20data%2C%20techniques%20for%20writing%20software%20that%20process%20data%20on%20a%20variety%20of%20computing%20platforms%2C%20protocols%20for%20communicating%20data%20reliably%20and%20securely%20across%20networks%2C%20the%20organization%20of%20data%20in%20databases%20of%20various%20types%20and%20scales%2C%20the%20emulation%20of%20human%20intelligence%20and%20learning%20through%20computer%20algorithms%2C%20statistical%20modeling%20of%20data%20in%20large%20databases%20to%20support%20inference%20of%20trends%2C%20and%20techniques%20for%20protecting%20the%20content%20and%20authenticity%20of%20data.%20Therefore%2C%20computer%20scientists%20are%20scientists%20and%20mathematicians%20who%20develop%20ways%20to%20process%2C%20interpret%2C%20store%2C%20communicate%2C%20and%20secure%20data.\",\"rhsI\":\"Computer%20Engineering%20is%20theintegration%20of%20Computer%20Science%20and%20Electrical%20Engineering.%20It%20focuses%20on%20computing%20in%20all%20forms%2C%20from%20microprocessors%20to%20embedded%20computing%20devices%20to%20laptop%20and%20desktop%20systems%20to%20supercomputers.%20As%20such%2C%20it%20concerns%20the%20electrical%20engineering%20considerations%20of%20how%20microprocessors%20function%2C%20are%20designed%2C%20and%20are%20optimized%3B%20how%20data%20is%20communicated%20among%20electronic%20components%3B%20how%20integrated%20systems%20of%20electronic%20components%20are%20designed%20and%20how%20they%20operate%20to%20process%20instructions%20expressed%20in%20software%3B%20and%20how%20software%20is%20written%2C%20compiled%2C%20and%20optimized%20for%20specific%20hardware%20platforms.%20Therefore%2C%20computer%20engineers%20are%20electrical%20engineers%20who%20specialize%20in%20software%20design%2C%20hardware%20design%2C%20or%20systems%20design%20that%20integrates%20both.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Overlap\",\"lhsI\":\"%3Cbr%20/%3EBecause%20both%20Computer%20Engineers%20and%20Computer%20Scientists%20ultimately%20work%20with%20data%20and%20attempt%20ultimately%20to%20harness%20meaning%20from%20it%2C%20there%20is%20significant%20overlap%20in%20coursework%20that%20students%20in%20the%20two%20fields%20take%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20careers%20they%20pursue.%20This%20does%20not%20minimize%20the%20distinctive%20nature%20of%20the%20two%20disciplines.%20It%20simply%20acknowledges%20the%20fact%20that%20these%20types%20of%20computer%20professionals%20find%20context%20and%20purpose%20in%20similar%20kinds%20of%20projects%20or%20in%20different%20aspects%20of%20the%20same%20kinds%20of%20projects.\",\"rhsI\":\"\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Studies \",\"lhsI\":\"At%20the%20undergraduate%20level%2C%20programs%20usually%20cover%20a%20broad%20range%20of%20computing%20topics%28theory%2C%20algorithms%2C%20programming%20languages%2C%20and%20architecture%29%20and%20allow%20students%20to%20engage%20in%20projects%20across%20multiple%20areas.%20For%20graduate%20studies%20in%20computer%20science%2C%20it%20is%20typical%20to%20focus%20on%20one%20area.\",\"rhsI\":\"Many%20people%20who%20want%20to%20become%20computer%20engineers%20earn%20an%20undergraduate%20degree%20in%20electrical%20engineering%20%28often%20with%20a%20minor%20or%20double%20major%20in%20computer%20science%29%2C%20and%20then%20earn%20a%20graduate%20degree%20in%20computer%20engineering.\"}]</p>\n', 'Answer for What is the difference between Computer Science &amp; Computer Technology?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', 