(3431, 25, '2017-02-26 20:33:53', '2017-02-26 20:33:53', '<p>[{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Introduction\",\"lhsI\":\"VoLTE%2C%20Voice%20over%20LTE%26nbsp%3Band%20VoWiFi%2C%20Voice%20over%20WiFi%20are%20two%20of%20three%20%22common%22%20solutions%20for%20Voice%20handling%20in%20LTE.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EDue%20the%20nature%20of%20LTE/EPC%20Network%20as%20a%20completely%20All-IP%26nbsp%3BMobile%20Data%20Network%2C%20the%20two%26nbsp%3Bsolutions%20were%20standardised%20to%20deliver%20voice%20services%20in%20LTE%20%28e.g.%20Voice%20Calling%29%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20Solution%20of%20CSFB%20%28Circuit%20Switched%20Fallback%29.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EBelow%20is%20a%20high-level%20digram%20that%20illustrates%20the%20Voice%20handling%20in%20LTE.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cimg%20style%3D%22width%3A%20100%25%3B%20height%3A%20auto%3B%22%20src%3D%22../../wp-content/plugins/custom-qa/images/blobid1488141177428.png%22%20alt%3D%22%22%20/%3E\",\"rhsI\":\"VoWiFi%2C%20Voice%20over%20WiFi%20is%20a%20term%20that%20describes%20the%20solution%20to%20deliver%26nbsp%3B%22Voice%22%20Services%20under%20WiFi%20Coverage%20with%20specific%20conditions.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Theory\",\"lhsI\":\"Voice%20over%20LTE%20is%20an%20IMS-based%20Solution%20that%20enables%20operators%20to%20migrate%20legacy%20Voice%20service%20to%20LTE%20Network%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20introduction%20of%20new%20Multimedia%20Services%20on%20LTE%20network.%20%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EVoLTE%20relies%20on%20the%20concept%20of%20dedicated%20bearer%20is%20LTE%20where%20the%20LTE%20user%20is%20granted%20a%20average%20QoS%20default%20bearer%20whenever%20the%20handset%20is%20turned%20on%20%22Attached%22%20enabling%20the%20user%20to%20register%20for%20IMS%20Services%20%28IMS%3A%20IP%20Multimedia%20Subsytem%29%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EWhenever%20the%20user%20initiates%20a%20call%20or%20receive%20a%20call%2C%20a%20dedicated%20bearer%20is%20triggered%20by%20the%20network%20with%20Voice-set%20quality%20of%20service%20thi