(3446, 40, '2017-03-01 11:29:53', '2017-03-01 11:29:53', '<p>[{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Definition\",\"lhsI\":\"Its%20first%20IETF%20RFC%202138%20was%20published%20in%201997.%20This%20RFC%20was%20obsoleted%20by%20RFC%202865.%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3ESimple%20and%20efficient%20solution%20for%20AAA%20%26ndash%3B%20Client/server%20model%20%26ndash%3B%20UDP%20transport%20%26ndash%3B%20Authentication%20and%20Authorization%20combined%20in%20a%20single%20transaction%20%28RFC%202865%29%20%26ndash%3B%20Accounting%20report%20sent%20at%20the%20beginning%20and%20the%20end%20of%20the%20access%20session%20%28RFC%202866%29%20%26ndash%3B%20Information%20data%20carried%20in%20Attributes%20in%20the%20TLV%20format%20%28%7CType%7CLength%7CValue%26hellip%3B%7C%29%20%26ndash%3B%20Simple%20routing%20based%20on%20pre-configured%20IP%20address\",\"rhsI\":\"Diameter%20was%20designed%20to%20be%20the%20successor%20of%20RADIUS%20%26bull%3B%20The%20name%20is%20a%20play%20on%20words%20Diameter%20%3D%20Twice%20the%20RADIUS%20%26bull%3B%20the%20name%20comes%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20As%20the%20identifier%20field%20of%20RADIUS%20is%208%20bits%20long%2C%20RADIUS%20can%20in%20principle%20have%20only%20256%20pending%20request%20at%20the%20same%20time%20and%20the%20max%20number%20of%20attributes%20is%20256.%20For%20Diameter%20with%20its%2032-bit%20field%20the%20theoretical%20maximum%20pending%20request%20and%20number%20of%20attributes%20is%20over%204%20billion%20%282%5E32%29..%20Hence%2C%20Diameter%20is%20not%20an%20acronym%20and%20it%20should%20not%20be%20written%20in%20CAPITAL%20letters.%21%21%21%3Cbr%20/%3E%3Cbr%20/%3EThe%20Diameter%20base%20protocol%20is%20defined%20by%26nbsp%3BRFC%206733%26nbsp%3B%28Obsoletes%3A%26nbsp%3BRFC%203588%29%26nbsp%3B%3Cbr%20/%3E\"},{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"Packet format\",\"lhsI\":\"The%20basic%20format%20of%20RADIUS%20and%20Diameter%20packets%20is%20similar.%20They%20include%20first%20a%20fixed%20size%20header%2C%20and%20after%20that%20a%20variable%20number%20of%20attributes%2C%20which%20are%20generally%20referred%20to%20as%20AVPs%20%28Attribute%20Value%20Pairs%29\",\"rhsI\":\"\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Security\",\"lhsI\":\"A%20secret%20is%20shared%20between%20client%20and%20server%20%26bull%3B%20Used%20to%20generate%20cryptographic%20hash%20values%20%28using%20MD5%29%20to%20authenticate%20RADIUS%20messages%20%26bull%3B%20Used%20also%20to%20encrypt%20the%20user%20password%20between%20the%20client%20and%20the%20RADIUS%20server%20%26ndash%3B%20The%20user%27s%20password%20is%20never%20sent%20in%20clear-text%20in%20the%20network.\",\"rhsI\":\"Diameter%20security%20is%20provided%20by%26nbsp%3BIPsec%26nbsp%3Bor%26nbsp%3BTLS.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Transport\",\"lhsI\":\"RADIUS%20runs%20over%20UDP%20%28User%20Datagram%20Protocol%29\",\"rhsI\":\"Diameter%20can%20use%20either%20SCTP%20%28Stream%20Control%20Transmission%20Protocol%29%20or%20TCP%20%28Transmission%20Control%20Protocol%29.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Server-initiated messages\",\"lhsI\":\"Support%20for%20server-initiated%20messages%20%28for%20re-authentication%20e.g.%29%20is%20optional%20in%20RADIUS.\",\"rhsI\":\"Support%20for%20server-initiated%20messages%20%28for%20re-authentication%20e.g.%29%20is%20mandatory%20in%20Diameter.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Capability negotiation\",\"lhsI\":\"RADIUS%20does%20not%20support%20error%20messages%2C%20capability%20negotiation%2C%20or%20a%20mandatory/non-mandatory%20flag%20for%20attributes.\",\"rhsI\":\"Capability%20negotiation%20is%20supported%20in%20Diameter\"},{\"cellsNumber\":2,\"row\":\"Peer discovery and Configuration\",\"lhsI\":\"RADIUS%20deployment%20requires%20that%20the%20name%20or%20address%20of%20servers%20or%20clients%20be%20manually%20configured%2C%20along%20with%20the%20corresponding%20shared%20secrets\",\"rhsI\":\"Through%20DNS%2C%20Diameter%20enables%20dynamic%20discovery%20of%20peers.\"},{\"cellsNumber\":1,\"row\":\"AAA\",\"lhsI\":\"RADIUS%20%28Remote%20Authentication%20Dial%20In%20User%20Service%29%20and%20Diameter%20are%20both%20protocols%20for%20AAA%20%28Authentication%2C%20Authorization%2C%20and%20Accounting%29%20control.\",\"rhsI\":\"\"}]</p>\n', 'Answer for What is the difference between RADIUS &amp; Diameter?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-radius-diameter', '', '', '2017-03-01 12:01:18', '2017-03-01 12:01:18', '', 3444, 'http://localhost/wp/dwqa-answer/answer-for-what-is-the-difference-between-radius-diameter/', 0, 'dwqa-answer', '', 1),
